<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>With this model, a primary event broker provides messaging services to clients, while a backup event broker waits in standby mode—it only provides service should the primary event broker fail. A third event broker acts as a monitoring node, to act as a tie-breaker and prevent split-brain scenarios that would otherwise cause both the primary and backup event broker to become active simultaneously.</body>
</html>